      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Line a 23 x 33 cm tin with baking paper. Whisk the melted butter, caster sugar, and dark brown sugar together in a large bowl until combined. Beat in the eggs and vanilla. Stir in the flour, bicarbonate of soda, and salt until just combined. Fold in the chocolate chips.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Tip the dough into the prepared tin and press firmly into an even layer with lightly dampened hands. Bake for 22 to 26 minutes until the top is golden and set at the edges and the centre looks slightly underdone. Cool completely in the tin before lifting out and cutting into bars. For the cleanest cuts, refrigerate for 15 minutes before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
